About Me

I'm a Computer Engineering student at Michigan State University (class of 2026) with a passion for AI-powered full-stack development. My work spans deep-learning research, data-driven back-ends, and pixel-perfect React front-ends.

Over the last four years I've shipped award-winning projects at national hackathons, led a non-profit tech startup from 3 to 12 engineers, and open-sourced tools used by hundreds of developers. I believe in clean, maintainable code and user-first design.

When I'm not coding you'll find me mentoring fellow hackers, experimenting with edge-AI on Raspberry Pi, or hunting for the best coffee in East Lansing. I'm always eager to collaborate on ambitious ideas.
